DCI officers have launched a probe into the death of a 15-year-old girl who was allegedly assaulted by her parents and brother for running away from their Kilimani home.  According to police reports, the trio is reported to have fatally assaulted the teenager after they accused her of running away from home.  Detectives visited the suspects' house in Nairobi's Kilimani area and arrested them following the Thursday night incident.  “The three suspects have been placed in custody at Kilimani Police Station,” said DCI on Saturday, May 22.  DCI: How rogue prison warder conned Kenyans over Sh200m in fake jobs deal  Senior DCI officers reshuffled (list)  MP wants detective queried in fraud case  Senior DCI officer shoots dead security guard in Kayole During the arrest, the Kilimani-based detectives also recovered one PPR pipe believed to have been used to beat up the deceased and is being held as an exhibit.  “Officers who visited the scene recovered one PPR pipe believed to have been used to beat up the deceased.”  Norine Mwende, a clinical officer at the Coptic hospital told detectives that the girl’s body had bruises all over.  Take a quick survey and help us improve our website! The body is awaiting postmortem at the Coptic hospital morgue.   Kemsa Probe: Former EACC CEO Waqo grilled  Journalist in judge Philip Tunoi bribery allegations Geoffrey Kiplagat cross examined  Suspended Youth fund CEO Catherine Namuye grilled By Mireri Junior | 4 hours ago By PSCU | 17 hours ago By Kamore Maina | 22 hours ago By Graham Kajilwa | 2 days ago